---
import GetStartedLayout from "../../layouts/GetStartedLayout.astro";
import DocH2WithAnchor from "../../components/DocH2WithAnchor.astro";
---

<GetStartedLayout
  title="Design language"
  current="language"
  showAnchorsAside
  description="Design intent, perceptual principles, visual dials, core behaviors, and how the system implements this language."
>
  <div slot="lead">
    <header class="page-head">
      <h1 data-i18n="getStarted.language.h2">Design language</h1>
      <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.lede">
        The design language is the personality of the system: how Prism looks, reads, and moves together. Intent,
        perceptual principles, visual dials, and behaviors that keep collaboration calm, clear, and trustworthy.
      </p>
    </header>
    <figure class="lang-intro-placeholder">
      <img
        class="lang-intro-placeholder__img"
        src="/images/get-started/design-language-intro-placeholder.png"
        width="640"
        height="360"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        data-i18n-alt="getStarted.language.introPlaceholderAlt"
        alt="Neutral placeholder for a future design language illustration."
      />
    </figure>
  </div>

  <div class="lang-article-sections">
  <section class="lang-section lang-doc" aria-labelledby="lang-s0">
    <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s0" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s0.h2">Eric's Design Principles</DocH2WithAnchor>
    <ul class="lang-list">
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s0.li1">Less UI elements</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s0.li2">Fewer clicks</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s0.li3">No hidden logic</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s0.li4">Don't make users think</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="lang-section lang-doc" aria-labelledby="lang-s1">
    <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s1" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s1.h2">Design Intent</DocH2WithAnchor>
    <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s1.p1">
      Our design language expresses calm confidence in moments that matter.
    </p>
    <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s1.p2">
      It balances precision and warmth so people feel in control, understood, and focused while collaborating in high-stakes meetings.
    </p>
    <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s1.p3">
      Meetings are often stressful, time-sensitive, and socially complex. Our visual language should reduce cognitive load, signal trust, and quietly support human connection — without drawing attention to itself.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lang-section lang-doc" aria-labelledby="lang-s2">
    <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s2" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.h2">Perceptual Principles</DocH2WithAnchor>
    <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.intro">
      These principles define how the product should feel, not what it looks like.
    </p>

    <div class="lang-perceptual">
      <section class="lang-perceptual-block" aria-labelledby="lang-s2-calm">
        <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s2-calm" level={3} data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.calm.h3">Calm Authority</DocH2WithAnchor>
        <p class="intro lead" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.calm.lead">
          The product should feel reliable and steady, even under pressure.
        </p>
        <div class="lang-pair-grid">
          <div>
            <p class="lang-pair-label" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.isLabel">Is</p>
            <ul class="lang-list lang-list--tight lang-list--pair-affirm">
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.calm.is1">Clear hierarchy</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.calm.is2">Predictable behavior</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.calm.is3">Visual stability</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="lang-pair-label" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.isNotLabel">Is not</p>
            <ul class="lang-list lang-list--tight lang-list--pair-negate">
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.calm.not1">Loud, attention-seeking UI</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.calm.not2">Overly playful aesthetics</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.calm.not3">Frequent visual surprises</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="lang-perceptual-block" aria-labelledby="lang-s2-human">
        <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s2-human" level={3} data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.human.h3">Human, Not Casual</DocH2WithAnchor>
        <p class="intro lead" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.human.lead">
          We support real people in real work without being flippant.
        </p>
        <div class="lang-pair-grid">
          <div>
            <p class="lang-pair-label" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.isLabel">Is</p>
            <ul class="lang-list lang-list--tight lang-list--pair-affirm">
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.human.is1">Warm, respectful tone</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.human.is2">Subtle personality</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.human.is3">Considered use of friendliness</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="lang-pair-label" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.isNotLabel">Is not</p>
            <ul class="lang-list lang-list--tight lang-list--pair-negate">
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.human.not1">Cute</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.human.not2">Ironic</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.human.not3">Informal to the point of undermining trust</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="lang-perceptual-block" aria-labelledby="lang-s2-focus">
        <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s2-focus" level={3} data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.focus.h3">Effortless Focus</DocH2WithAnchor>
        <p class="intro lead" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.focus.lead">
          The interface fades away so the meeting can take center stage.
        </p>
        <div class="lang-pair-grid">
          <div>
            <p class="lang-pair-label" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.isLabel">Is</p>
            <ul class="lang-list lang-list--tight lang-list--pair-affirm">
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.focus.is1">Purposeful minimalism</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.focus.is2">Strong defaults</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.focus.is3">Reduced decision-making</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="lang-pair-label" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.isNotLabel">Is not</p>
            <ul class="lang-list lang-list--tight lang-list--pair-negate">
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.focus.not1">Feature-heavy surfaces</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.focus.not2">Competing visual elements</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.focus.not3">Decorative UI without function</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="lang-perceptual-block" aria-labelledby="lang-s2-pmotion">
        <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s2-pmotion" level={3} data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.pmotion.h3">Purposeful Motion</DocH2WithAnchor>
        <p class="intro lead" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.pmotion.lead">
          Motion explains cause and effect and reinforces understanding.
        </p>
        <div class="lang-pair-grid">
          <div>
            <p class="lang-pair-label" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.isLabel">Is</p>
            <ul class="lang-list lang-list--tight lang-list--pair-affirm">
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.pmotion.is1">Intentional</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.pmotion.is2">Subtle</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.pmotion.is3">Functional</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="lang-pair-label" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.isNotLabel">Is not</p>
            <ul class="lang-list lang-list--tight lang-list--pair-negate">
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.pmotion.not1">Decorative</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.pmotion.not2">Fast for the sake of speed</li>
              <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s2.pmotion.not3">Distracting during conversation</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lang-section lang-doc" aria-labelledby="lang-s3">
    <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s3" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.h2">Visual Dial Settings</DocH2WithAnchor>
    <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.p1">
      Our design language lives on a spectrum. These settings guide future decisions.
    </p>
    <div class="lang-table-wrap">
      <table class="lang-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.thDial">Dial</th>
            <th scope="col" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.thPosition">Position</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r1dial">Expressive ←→ Restrained</td>
            <td data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r1pos">Restrained</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r2dial">Friendly ←→ Formal</td>
            <td data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r2pos">Balanced, slightly formal</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r3dial">Light ←→ Dense</td>
            <td data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r3pos">Moderately light</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r4dial">Neutral ←→ Opinionated</td>
            <td data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r4pos">Quietly opinionated</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r5dial">Static ←→ Dynamic</td>
            <td data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r5pos">Mostly static, selectively dynamic</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <figure class="lang-spectrum-figure">
      <figcaption class="lang-spectrum-caption">
        <span data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.spectrumTitle">Spectrum</span>
        ·
        <span data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.spectrumColPos">Position</span>
      </figcaption>
      <div class="lang-spectrum-rows">
        <div class="lang-spectrum-row">
          <pre class="lang-spectrum-pre" aria-hidden="true">{`Expressive
←─────────────────────────────⭐️→
Restrained`}</pre>
          <p class="lang-spectrum-pos" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r1pos">Restrained</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lang-spectrum-row">
          <pre class="lang-spectrum-pre" aria-hidden="true">{`Friendly
←────────────────────⭐️─────────→
Formal`}</pre>
          <p class="lang-spectrum-pos" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r2pos">Balanced, slightly formal</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lang-spectrum-row">
          <pre class="lang-spectrum-pre" aria-hidden="true">{`Light
←───────────⭐️──────────────────→
Dense`}</pre>
          <p class="lang-spectrum-pos" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r3pos">Moderately light</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lang-spectrum-row">
          <pre class="lang-spectrum-pre" aria-hidden="true">{`Neutral
←─────────────────────────⭐️────→
Opinionated`}</pre>
          <p class="lang-spectrum-pos" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r4pos">Quietly opinionated</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lang-spectrum-row">
          <pre class="lang-spectrum-pre" aria-hidden="true">{`Static
←─────⭐️──────────────────────────→
Dynamic`}</pre>
          <p class="lang-spectrum-pos" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.r5pos">Mostly static, selectively dynamic</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </figure>

    <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s3.note">
      These dials should be revisited annually, not per project.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lang-section lang-doc" aria-labelledby="lang-s4">
    <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s4" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.h2">Core Visual Behaviors</DocH2WithAnchor>

    <section class="lang-subsection" aria-labelledby="lang-s4-layout">
      <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s4-layout" level={3} data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.layout.h3">Layout & Space</DocH2WithAnchor>
      <ul class="lang-list">
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.layout.p1">Layouts prioritize stability over novelty</li>
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.layout.p2">Primary actions are visually anchored and predictable</li>
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.layout.p3">Whitespace is used to create calm and separation, not luxury</li>
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.layout.p4">
          Density scales intentionally for enterprise power users without overwhelming new users
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.layout.guide">
        Guiding idea: If everything is emphasized, nothing is.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="lang-subsection" aria-labelledby="lang-s4-color">
      <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s4-color" level={3} data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.color.h3">Color</DocH2WithAnchor>
      <ul class="lang-list">
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.color.p1">Color is functional first, expressive second</li>
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.color.p2">Primary brand color signals focus and action</li>
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.color.p3">Neutral surfaces dominate to support long-duration use</li>
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.color.p4">Accent colors are used sparingly to convey status, not decoration</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.color.rule">
        🎨 Color should never compete with 👩‍🏫 people's faces or 📃 shared content.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="lang-subsection" aria-labelledby="lang-s4-type">
      <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s4-type" level={3} data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.type.h3">Typography</DocH2WithAnchor>
      <ul class="lang-list">
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.type.p1">Typography communicates confidence through clarity</li>
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.type.p2">Hierarchy is obvious at a glance</li>
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.type.p3">Text supports scanning and quick comprehension</li>
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.type.p4">Type should feel contemporary, not trendy</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.type.rule">
        Typography should never feel decorative or experimental in core meeting flows.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="lang-subsection" aria-labelledby="lang-s4-motion">
      <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s4-motion" level={3} data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.motion.h3">Motion</DocH2WithAnchor>
      <ul class="lang-list">
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.motion.p1">Motion reinforces system feedback and spatial relationships</li>
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.motion.p2">Transitions are short, smooth, and predictable</li>
        <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.motion.p3">Motion is reduced or removed during active meetings</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="intro">
        <strong data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.motion.ruleLabel">Rule of thumb:</strong>{" "}
        <span data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s4.motion.rule">
          If motion distracts during conversation, it does not belong in the meeting experience.
        </span>
      </p>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section class="lang-section lang-doc" aria-labelledby="lang-s5">
    <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s5" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s5.h2">Iconography</DocH2WithAnchor>
    <ul class="lang-list">
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s5.p1">Icons are simple, recognizable, and consistent in metaphor</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s5.p2">
        Filled vs outlined styles are used intentionally, not mixed arbitrarily (outline first)
      </li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s5.p3">Icons should read clearly at small sizes and low attention</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s5.p4">Icons explain actions, not brand personality.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="lang-section lang-doc" aria-labelledby="lang-s6">
    <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s6" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.h2">Illustration & Graphic Language (Empty States, Education)</DocH2WithAnchor>
    <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.p1">
      Illustrations support understanding, reassurance, and guidance — especially when something is missing or incomplete.
    </p>
    <p class="lang-mini-h" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.purpose">Purpose</p>
    <ul class="lang-list">
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.purpose1">Explain system states</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.purpose2">Reduce anxiety during errors or empty states</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.purpose3">Guide users toward next actions</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="lang-mini-h" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.style">Style</p>
    <ul class="lang-list">
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.style1">Abstracted, not literal</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.style2">Minimal detail</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.style3">Subtle depth</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.style4">Neutral perspective</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="lang-mini-h" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.tone">Tone</p>
    <ul class="lang-list">
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.tone1">Supportive</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.tone2">Intelligent</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.tone3">Calm</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.close1">Illustrations are not decorative art.</p>
    <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s6.close2">
      If the UI communicates clearly without one, an illustration is not required.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lang-section lang-doc" aria-labelledby="lang-s7">
    <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s7" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s7.h2">Content & Voice Alignment</DocH2WithAnchor>
    <ul class="lang-list">
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s7.p1">Language is clear, concise, and respectful</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s7.p2">Avoid jokes, slang, or cultural references</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s7.p3">Error messages explain what happened and what to do next</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s7.p4">The system speaks as a helpful professional, not a mascot</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="lang-section lang-doc" aria-labelledby="lang-s8">
    <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s8" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s8.h2">Decision Filters</DocH2WithAnchor>
    <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s8.intro">All design work should pass these checks:</p>
    <ol class="lang-checklist">
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s8.q1">Does this increase clarity in a high-pressure moment?</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s8.q2">Does this reduce cognitive load or add to it?</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s8.q3">Would this feel appropriate in a serious enterprise setting?</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s8.q4">Does this reinforce calm and control?</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s8.q5">Is this solving a real user problem — or decorating it?</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s8.close">
      If a design fails two or more filters, it needs revision.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lang-section lang-doc" aria-labelledby="lang-s9">
    <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s9" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s9.h2">Relationship to the Design System</DocH2WithAnchor>
    <ul class="lang-list">
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s9.p1">The design system is the mechanical implementation of this language.</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s9.p2">Tokens express our visual decisions</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s9.p3">Components embody our principles</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s9.p4">Patterns reinforce consistency and predictability</li>
      <li data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s9.p5">
        Components may evolve, but they must always reinforce the perceptual principles defined here.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="lang-section lang-doc" aria-labelledby="lang-s10">
    <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s10" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s10.h2">Personas / User types</DocH2WithAnchor>
    <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s10.intro">
      We plan for user buckets from inclusive first-time use through expert efficiency. Levels describe breadth of need, not value.
    </p>
    <section class="lang-persona" aria-labelledby="lang-s10-l1">
      <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s10-l1" level={3} data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s10.l1h">
        Level 1 — Broad reach (about 8 to 80)
      </DocH2WithAnchor>
      <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s10.l1b">
        Core flows stay legible and forgiving for a wide age range; grandparents (and others less familiar with software) should be able to complete primary tasks without jargon or mystery mechanics.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section class="lang-persona" aria-labelledby="lang-s10-l2">
      <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s10-l2" level={3} data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s10.l2h">
        Level 2 — People in between
      </DocH2WithAnchor>
      <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s10.l2b">
        The majority of collaborators: comfortable with common patterns, balancing speed with clarity. Defaults and hierarchy do most of the teaching.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section class="lang-persona" aria-labelledby="lang-s10-l3">
      <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s10-l3" level={3} data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s10.l3h">
        Level 3 — Advanced collaborators
      </DocH2WithAnchor>
      <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s10.l3b">
        Frequent enterprise users who need density, shortcuts, and predictable muscle memory — without sacrificing calm or trust on shared surfaces.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section class="lang-persona" aria-labelledby="lang-s10-l4">
      <DocH2WithAnchor
      class="doc-tabs__h2 article-article__section-title"
      rowClass="doc-h2-anchor-row--tabs"
      id="lang-s10-l4" level={3} data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s10.l4h">
        Level 4 — Superusers
      </DocH2WithAnchor>
      <p class="intro" data-i18n="getStarted.language.doc.s10.l4b">
        Keyboard-first workflows, customization, and maximum throughput where appropriate; power features must not hijack the baseline experience for Levels 1–2.
      </p>
    </section>
  </section>
